id: jf-cqqy
title: Fix live username/password authentication contract
description: "The client sends AuthenticateByName without Jellyfin client-identification metadata, models the AuthenticationResult response as UserDto, and never installs AccessToken for subsequent requests. Live Jellyfin 10.11.11 returns HTTP 400 before the current mocked unit test can detect the contract error."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[6]: api,auth,e2e,openapi,regression,security
created_at: "2026-07-21T19:38:09.589Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-21T20:03:28.118Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-21T20:03:27.264Z"
author: codex-jellyfin
estimated_minutes: 120
acceptance_criteria: AuthenticateByName sends the Jellyfin MediaBrowser client header required by the server; The exact 10.11.11 AuthenticationResult wrapper is fully typed without any; Successful authentication stores AccessToken and User.Id for subsequent requests and modules; Username/password ENV auth succeeds through the compiled jf-cli under read-only mode; Unit tests assert request headers response unwrapping token propagation and structured failures
goal: jf-mqpo
value: Make the documented username/password setup path actually usable.
impact: Restores setup wizard and ENV authentication for users who do not provide an API key.
outcome: Correct typed authentication followed by authenticated read-only CLI calls.
why_now: The requested live credential proof failed with HTTP 400 and exposed a mocked-test blind spot.
parent: jf-gn5j
reviewer: maintainer
risk: critical
confidence: high
sprint: jellyfin-10.11.11
reporter: codex-jellyfin
severity: critical
environment: Jellyfin 10.11.11 compiled jf-cli with JELLYFIN_USERNAME and JELLYFIN_PASSWORD
repro_steps: Use a clean JELLYFIN_CONFIG_DIR set server URL username and password via ENV and run jf-cli --format json users me; observe Authentication failed API request failed 400 Bad Request.
resolution: "AuthenticateByName now sends MediaBrowser client identity, validates and installs AccessToken, records User.Id, and synchronizes every API facade module."
expected_result: Username/password-only automation authenticates and performs subsequent read-only calls.
actual_result: Contract tests pass and a clean environment-only compiled jf-cli session authenticated successfully against the local server without persisting credentials.
affected_version: 2026.7.21-3
component: api-auth
regression: true
customer_impact: All username/password-only setup and runtime flows fail against the live server.
