comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T19:38:09.589Z",codex-jellyfin,Discovered during required live read-only ENV authentication after API-key setup validation and 177 compiled E2E checks passed.
  "2026-07-21T19:40:42.667Z",codex-jellyfin,"Live repair proof passed: a clean config directory with only server URL username and password in ENV authenticated through the rebuilt global jf-cli and returned a current-user record under JELLYFIN_READ_ONLY=1."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T19:38:09.589Z",codex-jellyfin,"Authoritative source: local 10.11.11 OpenAPI /Users/AuthenticateByName returns components.schemas.AuthenticationResult with User SessionInfo AccessToken and ServerId."
learnings[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T19:38:09.589Z",codex-jellyfin,Mocking the endpoint as a UserDto allowed both the missing client header and wrong response envelope to pass; contract fixtures must come from the exact OpenAPI schema.
  "2026-07-21T19:40:43.552Z",codex-jellyfin,Jellyfin requires a MediaBrowser client-identification Authorization header even before an access token exists; API-key-only tests masked this prerequisite. AuthenticationResult.User and AccessToken must both be validated before updating client state.
